00:51:22,411 --> 00:51:27,670
I knew the music was loud because I fell the
vibration of the sound in the floor under

974
00:51:27,670 --> 00:51:31,120
my feet- Mum put her hands over her ears.

975
00:51:31,120 --> 00:51:35,440
When Jim saw me there was not as much vibration
because he stopped playing his drums.

976
00:51:35,440 --> 00:51:40,020
He got up and walked over to me and his friends
stopped playing too.

977
00:51:40,020 --> 00:51:43,350
I think everyone was looking at us, but I'm
not sure.

978
00:51:43,350 --> 00:51:48,500
All I remember is Jims smile and the love
in his eyes before he kissed me.

979
00:51:48,500 --> 00:51:52,310
As I kissed him back, I forgot to be afraid.

980
00:51:52,310 --> 00:51:54,780
This was Jim and I loved him.

981
00:51:54,780 --> 00:51:57,600
There was nothing to be afraid of.

982
00:51:57,600 --> 00:52:02,330
After a few moments he moved about a metre
away and started to sign to me.

983
00:52:02,330 --> 00:52:04,811
He made some mistakes, but I understood.

984
00:52:04,811 --> 00:52:08,450
Just as he understood when I spoke to him.

985
00:52:08,450 --> 00:52:11,460
And I remembered his fast hands on the drums...

986
00:52:11,460 --> 00:52:13,880
There was no problem.

987
00:52:13,880 --> 00:52:17,930
This is what he signed to me: 'Your mum taught
me some sign language.

988
00:52:17,930 --> 00:52:21,340
Now I'll teach you to play drums.

989
00:52:21,340 --> 00:52:23,800
Come with me.'

990
00:52:23,800 --> 00:52:27,300
Before I could answer, Jim took my hand in
his.

991
00:52:27,300 --> 00:52:30,210
We moved to stand with his friends.

992
00:52:30,210 --> 00:52:32,060
Mum was smiling at me.

993
00:52:32,060 --> 00:52:33,890
Everyone was smiling.

994
00:52:33,890 --> 00:52:39,600
Jim stood behind me and his hands were on
my hands and then I was playing the drums.

995
00:52:39,600 --> 00:52:44,370
And the vibration travelled from the drums
to my hands and up my arms to my head.

996
00:52:44,370 --> 00:52:45,530
It was wonderful.

997
00:52:45,530 --> 00:52:51,790
As wonderful as my small hand on the front
of Mum's guitar.

998
00:52:51,790 --> 00:52:52,240
- THE END -

